cials or pop music? And what can this debate contribute to science communication?  afunded by Gesellschaft von Freunden und Förderern der TU Dresden e.V.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aScience in popular culture. 4aCultural Studies. 4aKinofilm. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aPop. 4aPopkultur. 4aPopmusik. 4aScience Studies. 4aWerbung. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 4aWissenschaftskommunikation. 4aWissenschaftssoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAdvertising.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aHistory of Science.  aMedia.  aMotion Picture.  aPop Music.  aPop.  aScience Studies.  aScience.  aSociology of Science.1 aArenhövel, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeorgi-Findlay, Brigitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunkerjürgen, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühn, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühn, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKühn, Übersetzung Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNunokawa, Yasuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSanders, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScharlaj, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScharloth, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchrage, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStorey, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTroschitz, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTroschitz, Ro